> Please don't. Merging is just easier to do, makes it easier to see what changed and to keep track of reviews, doesn't destroy links ...

@jreback now I'm confused.  Yesterday I thought you were encouraging me to use "git rebase upstream/master" instead of "git pull upstream master".  The latter is what I've been doing all along (and did this morning).

<b>update</b> Woops, I assumed that the referenced comment was from jreback, didn't notice it was from @jorisvandenbossche.  No longer confused.
